body:
read it on the AO3 at https://ift.tt/2PXK8AY

by Ares00

At the end of the Avenger’s movie, Thor receives a dream message from Odin via Frigga that the Avengers must follow Thor and Loki to Asgard for his trial. The realms are convening with delegations of their own to judge Loki’s innocence or guilt, but the Avengers notice something strange.

Wasn’t Loki meant to be hated by the people? They why did the citizens show silent support?

body:

It’s called The Bend and Snap.
